news.title: Tamil Nadu: Draft coastal zone management plan out; feedback sought within a month
news.para: The map had indicated 11 categories of locations as 'no development zones'. They have been classified as ecosystems, geomorphological sites, habitats and heritage sites.

news.title: Archives department to digitise land papers to prevent fraud: Goa minister
news.para: Minister for archives Subhash Phal Dessai said that people have fraudulently used land documents from the archives department and claimed ownership on land.

news.title: Smartworks leases 1.7 lakh sq ft in Jaipur and Indore
news.para: Smartworks plans to add another three million sq ft this fiscal year, bringing its total portfolio to 10 million sq ft.

news.title: Kochi: Three satellite towns to be developed
news.para: According to the concept of the urban expansion presented by the GCDA the city centre would be retained as Parent City and it would be the developed as a first Sponge City in Kerala and three satellite towns would be developed.

news.title: JSW Cement to invest over Rs 3,200 crore to establish 5 MTPA cement capacity
news.para: The proposed investment includes an integrated cement plant with 2.5 MTPA clinker capacity, 2.5 MTPA grinding capacity, 15 MW Waste Heat Recovery System, a modern residential colony in Madhya Pradesh and a 2.5 MTPA grinding unit in Uttar Pradesh.

news.title: Sobha's sales bookings up 13% to Rs 1,164 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: In volume terms, sales bookings dropped to 13,36,828 square feet in July-September quarter of the 2022-23 fiscal year from 13,48,864 square feet in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Brigade Group appoints Pavitra Shankar as MD, Nirupa Shankar as joint MD
news.para: The board also approved the appointment of Aroon Raman, independent director, as non-executive vice chairman for the period October 11, 2022 to August 4, 2024.

news.title: Ahmedabad: ICICI Bank fined for losing couple's property documents
news.para: The case involved Himanshiben and Chaitanya Soni having a house in Umiyavijay Society in Jodhpur area. While obtaining credit facility from the bank in February 2005, they deposited the original sale-deed of their house and society's share certificate towards security.

news.title: Gujarat: 30-35% increase in sale deed registrations since Navratri
news.para: The officer has also ordered each sub-registrar office to issue 61 appointment tokens daily. There are 43 sub-registrar offices in the state that register property sale deeds, and 12 of these offices are in Ahmedabad.

news.title: Punjab CM approves hike in minimum wages of construction workers
news.para: The CM said minimum wages of unskilled workers have been hiked to Rs 9,907 from existing Rs 9,192 whereas that of semi-skilled have been enhanced to Rs 10,687 from Rs 9,972.

news.title: Tamil Nadu seeks time to submit report on registration of plots
news.para: The petitioner alleged that two people were selling residential plots in Veerapandi village in the district without obtaining layout approval from the executive officer of Veerapandi town panchayat.

news.title: Chandigarh estate office recovers Rs 85 crore dues since April 2022
news.para: The dues pertain to unpaid rent on leasehold properties, penalties on misuse of properties and building violations. Some of these dues were pending for last more than a decade.

news.title: Delhi LG launches portal for digital management of DDA's land records
news.para: ​The portal 'Land Management Information System' (LMIS) is also aimed at effective and efficient management and protection of DDA land records, said an official statement.

news.title: Raze illegal walls & farmhouses built in Faridabad Aravalis in 15 days, owners told
news.para: A total of 600 structures have been identified in Ankhir and Mewla Maharajpur villages, whereas ground truthing (an exercise to verify data collected through aerial photography or satellite radar via ground visits) of illegal structures is still going on in Anangpur and Lakkarpur villages.

news.title: In two decades, 2,253 maps approved in Ghaziabad but only 221 CCs given out
news.para: Data shared by the GDA showed that it had approved 2,253 building layouts in the past 18 years. But only 221 of these projects have CCs till date.
